== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Peel and dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1/2-inch pieces. (TIP: For speedier spud prep, skip the peeling.) Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain and return potatoes to pot.

Mash potatoes with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} using a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Caramelized Onion ==

While potatoes cook, heat a large drizzle of cooking oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1%tsp} and a splash of water; cook until caramelized, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Steak Diane ==

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of cooking oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

== Dijon-Mushroom Sauce ==

Add @butter{1%TBSP} and mushrooms to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @beef demi-glace{1}. Add @water{1/4%cup}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer.

> Use 1/3 cup water for 4 servings.

Stir in @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide potatoes, carrots, and steak between plates. Top potatoes with caramelized onion. Top steak with mushroom sauce and serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145º.